<h1 class="cd-text cd-title">ribbons</h1>
<p class="cd-text">ribbons are used to visually distinguish or "call out" items in a list. One example use case would be to highlight that a particular list item has a special status. They should only be used inside paragraphs or as standalone <code>&lt;span&gt;</code></p>

<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">inline</h2>
<p>ribbons work fine <span class="ribbon ribbon--feature">inline</span> because they take up the same space as regular paragraph text.</p>

<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">default</h2>
<p><span class="ribbon">ribbon</span></p>
{{#codeBlock 'xml margin-reset'}}
    <span class="ribbon">ribbon</span>
{{/codeBlock}}

<h2 class="cd-text cd-title">feature</h2>
<p><span class="ribbon ribbon--feature">feature</span></p>
{{#codeBlock 'xml margin-reset'}}
    <span class="ribbon ribbon--feature">feature</span>
{{/codeBlock}}

